rl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aWhat is the logic of the design process? Departing from this question and focusing on processes of invention and discovery, Tiago da Costa e Silva investigates the characteristic feature of every projective activity, for instance, in architecture, design, engineering design, and in the arts. In opposition to predominant views that understand design processes as mechanical, this study with the help of the semiotics of Charles S. Peirce characterizes design activities as a continuous and serendipitous interplay of processes of aesthetic experience, of defining rules, and of manifesting forms. Da Costa e Silva concludes that invention and discovery are intrinsic to every development in any given design context.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 4aAbductive Inference. 4aAesthetic Experience. 4aAesthetics. 4aCharles S. Peirce. 4aDesign. 4aDiscovery. 4aForm-Giving Process. 4aInvention. 4aLanguage. 4aMedia Aesthetics. 4aSemiotics. 4aSerendipity. 4aTheory of Art. 7aDESIGN / History & Criticism.2bisacsh  aAbductive Inference.  aAesthetic Experience.  aAesthetics.  aCharles S. Peirce.  aDesign.  aDiscovery.  aForm-Giving Process.  aInvention.  aLanguage.  aMedia Aesthetics.  aSemiotics.  aSerendipity.  aTheory of Art.1 ada Costa e Silva, Tiago, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2018z978311071955008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Architecture and Design 2018z9783110602999oZDB-23-DAD08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Arts, Architecture and Design 2018 Englishz978311060397208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 20